## Usage Examples

```bash
# Import from KB JSON file
theora ingest --from kb.json --tag space-program

# Import from plain text file
theora ingest --from urls.txt --tag nasa

# Import from stdin
cat kb.json | theora ingest --from -

# Export KB to JSON
theora export --format json > my-kb.json

# Round-trip test
theora export --format json | theora ingest --from - --tag imported
```

## Open Questions

1. Should we store Dublin Core metadata in the manifest, or just use it for import/export?
2. Should export include full content or just metadata?
3. Should we support partial updates (merge) or only full replacement?
4. Should we add a `--validate-only` flag to check JSON without ingesting?
